## Limitations and Risks

A few risks are worth naming up front. The continuous double auction is a simplified market, so a threshold found in simulation may not transfer directly to a live trading or lending system; we treat the result as a controlled-environment finding, not a deployment guarantee. Model behavior also shifts across versions, so a babble effect measured today may change as providers update their models, which is why we report results per model and per version rather than as universal claims. Finally, defining and detecting collusion in a free-form communication setting is itself nontrivial, so we rely on the price-based collusion index as the ground truth rather than trying to classify intent from the agents' messages.

